et%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECruise%20robotaxi%20%3C%2Fa%3Ewas%20involved%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcruise-driverless-car-robotaxi-runs-over-woman-san-francisco-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epedestrian%20accident%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20San%20Francisco.%20(The%20company%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftechcrunch.com%2F2023%2F12%2F14%2Fcruise-slashes-24-of-self-driving-car-workforce-in-sweeping-layoffs%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elaid%20off%2024%25%20of%20its%20workforce%3C%2Fa%3E.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20up%20for%20a%20promotion%2C%20and%20the%20team%20was%20preparing%20my%20new%20package.%20But%20I%20was%20let%20go%20from%20Cruise%2C%20and%20I%20got%20the%20news%20one%20day%20before%20my%20wife%20had%20our%20second%20child.%20There%20were%20complications%2C%20and%20my%20job%20was%20the%20last%20thing%20on%20my%20mind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20things%20started%20settling%2C%20I%20updated%20my%20LinkedIn%20to%20reflect%20%26quot%3BOpen%20to%20work%26quot%3B%20and%20started%20receiving%20messages%20from%20recruiters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20three%20things%20I%20did%20before%20my%20layoff%20and%20two%20steps%20I%20took%20after%20that%20helped%20me%20land%20a%20software%20engineer%20role%20at%20Meta%20within%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ee45539e-bccc-4a8c-a438-c3bc982fdb7e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20Maintaining%20relationships%20with%20recruiters%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20never%20intended%20to%20be%20polite%20to%20the%20recruiters%20who%20reached%20out%20to%20me%20while%20I%20was%20employed%20just%20so%20they%20could%20help%20with%20jobs%20down%20the%20line.%20But%2C%20I%20always%20responded%20to%20their%20reach%20outs%20on%20LinkedIn%20and%20replied%20that%20I'm%20not%20looking%20for%20a%20role%20right%20now%2C%20and%20asked%20them%20to%20keep%20in%20touch.%20Being%20responsive%20and%20staying%20connected%20may%20have%20helped%20the%20fact%20that%20recruiters%20for%20AirBnB%2C%20Meta%2C%20Uber%2C%20and%20Snowflake%20reached%20out%20with%20opportunities%20right%20after%20my%20layoff%20and%20limited%20the%20companies%20that%20I%20had%20to%20apply%20to%20myself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f9741df5-0da3-4bd7-bc6a-409d7e1e27ab%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Focusing%20on%20being%20a%20good%20engineer%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThroughout%20my%20career%2C%20I%20made%20it%20a%20priority%20to%20ask%20questions%20and%20not%20do%20my%20job%20like%20a%20mechanical%20task.%20Asking%20why%20things%20work%2C%20and%20why%20things%20are%20done%20the%20way%20they%20are%20made%20me%20a%20better%20engineer%2C%20and%20made%20it%20much%20easier%20for%20me%20to%20answer%20both%20technical%20and%20leadership%20questions%20at%20interviews%20even%20though%20my%20schedule%20was%20packed%20to%20the%20brim.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20also%20able%20to%20reach%20out%20to%20an%20ex-manager%20from%20my%20time%20at%20eBay%20who%20moved%20to%20Meta%20and%20ask%20him%20to%20refer%20me%2C%20because%20he%20remembered%20me%20and%20was%20happy%20to%20vouch%20for%20my%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228676ab7b-0adc-45cf-8e3e-1e52b4a51f95%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Domain%20variety%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20after%20my%20first%20layoff%2C%20I%20never%20tested%20the%20market%20every%20few%20years%20to%20gauge%20my%20worth.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-software-engineer-negotiated-salary-big-tech-meta-tesla-salesforce-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESwitching%20companies%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20always%20a%20last%20resort%2C%20and%20I%20only%20moved%20when%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20had%20exhausted%20my%20learning%20or%20when%20I%20no%20longer%20saw%20a%20work-life%20balance%20fit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20asked%20for%20internal%20transfers%20and%20joined%20growing%20companies%20where%20I%20could%20hone%20various%20domains.%20I%20moved%20from%20security%20to%20core%20infrastructure%20and%20then%20to%20infras